    "body": "### Problem\n\nAttempting to build Neovim fails at the linking stage due to missing pthread_getname_np symbol. I have installed all of the required packages - as described for Void Linux in the [BUILD.md](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/BUILD.md)\n\n```bash\n[petrside@voidlinux neovim]$ uname -r\n6.12.16_1\n```\n\n```bash\n[ 95%] Linking C executable ../../bin/nvim\n/usr/bin/ld: /home/petrside/github/neovim/.deps/usr/lib/libuv.a(thread.c.o): in function `uv__thread_getname':\n/home/petrside/github/neovim/.deps/build/src/libuv/src/unix/thread.c:967:(.text+0x509): undefined reference to `pthread_getname_np'\n/usr/bin/ld: /home/petrside/github/neovim/.deps/build/src/libuv/src/unix/thread.c:967:(.text+0xb7f): undefined reference to `pthread_getname_np'\ncollect2: error: ld returned 1 exit status\nmake[3]: *** [src/nvim/CMakeFiles/nvim_bin.dir/build.make:7876: bin/nvim] Error 1\nmake[2]: *** [CMakeFiles/Makefile2:676: src/nvim/CMakeFiles/nvim_bin.dir/all] Error 2\nmake[1]: *** [Makefile:156: all] Error 2\nmake[1]: Leaving directory '/home/petrside/github/neovim/build'\nmake: *** [Makefile:93: nvim] Error 2\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Clone the Neovim repository\n```bash\ngit clone --depth=1 git@github.com:neovim/neovim.git\n```\n2. Build the executable following [the instructions here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/BUILD.md)\n```bash\nmake CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo\n```\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTo build and link successfully.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nThe latest upstream master commit. [56fabca](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/56fabcadb6df46c70402e4f9cd1b851856fb57e9)\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nvoid linux kernel: 6.12.16_1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.15.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
