            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Although it is totally possible to compile Neovim on Void Linux on musl if you opt-out of the libuv and libluv bundled dependencies:\n```\ncmake -S cmake.deps -B .deps -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo -DUSE_BUNDLED=OFF -DUSE_BUNDLED_LIBUV=OFF -DUSE_BUNDLED_LUV=OFF -DUSE_BUNDLED_TS=ON -DUSE_BUNDLED_UTF8PROC=ON -DUSE_BUNDLED_LPEG=ON -DUSE_BUNDLED_TS_PARSERS=ON -DUSE_BUNDLED_UNIBILIUM=ON\n```\n\nAnd installing the system libuv and libluv dependencies, which don't need `pthread_getname_np`:\n```\nsudo xbps-install -S libluv-devel libuv-devel\n```",
